[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Mena-asia_default_banner.jpg"],["pgname=Tottori"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Japan_tottori_map_small.png"],["right"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Tottori prefecture"]}," (鳥取県 ",{"type":"''","value":["Tottori-ken"]},") is in the western ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Chugoku"]]}," region of the main ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Japan"]]},"ese island ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Honshu"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\nTottori prefecture, together with ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Shimane prefecture"]]}," is known as the ",{"type":"''","value":["Sanin"]}," region, meaning \"the shady side of the mountains\". There is a mountain range separating these two prefectures from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hiroshima (prefecture)"],["Hiroshima"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Okayama (prefecture)"],["Okayama"]]},", which means that the weather here is drastically wetter than further to the south.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Cities"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tottori"]]}," — The prefectural capital known for the Tottori Sand Dunes."]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kurayoshi"]]}," — A small town with a quaint retro shops and a well-preserved historic district."]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Daisen (Tottori)"],["Daisen"]]}," — The city of Daisen is home to ",{"type":"'''","value":["Mount Daisen"]},", a famous location for climbing, hiking, and skiing. The famous ",{"type":"'''","value":["Daisen-ji Temple"]}," is also located on this mountain."]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Misasa"]]},"  — Most famous for the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Mitokusan Nageiredo"]},", an old temple built on the side of a cliff. Nobody knows exactly how this temple was built, but it is a marvel to behold."]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Yurihama"]]}," —  A lovely city containing one of Japan's best Chinese gardens and Lake Togo."]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Yonago"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Sakai Minato"]]}," — Westernmost city in Tottori and home of Mizuki Shigeru, creator of ",{"type":"''","value":["Ge Ge Ge no Kitaro"]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hokuei"]]}," — Home to Aoyama World, the museum honoring Gosho Aoyama, the creator of Detective Conan."]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Other destinations"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Talk"]},"\t \n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By plane"]},"\nThere are three daily flights from Tokyo's Haneda airport to Tottori airport with ANA. The flight takes about 75 minutes. Tel. 0120-029-222, 0857-23-3038.\n",{"type":"===","value":["By train"]},"\nJR runs between ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Okayama"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tottori"],["Tottori City"]]},", and between ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Yonago"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Matsue"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Izumo"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By bus"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":["There is an express bus which runs from Tokyo's Hamamatsu-cho　to Tottori. The cost is about ￥10,200 one-way. Tel: 03-3743-0022"]},{"type":"*","value":["The bus from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Osaka"]]}," to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tottori"]]}," runs about 2 hours and 45 minutes, and costs about ￥7500."]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\t \n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" Hike on Mount Daisen to view the historic ",{"type":"'''","value":["Daisenji Temple"]}," (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Daisen (Tottori)"],["Daisen"]]},")"]},{"type":"*","value":[" Ride a camel along the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Tottori Sand Dunes"]}," (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tottori"]]},")"]},{"type":"*","value":[" Explore the mysterious ",{"type":"'''","value":["Mitokusan Nageiredo"]}," (Sanbutsuji Temple) (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Misasa"]]},")"]},{"type":"*","value":[" Take a walk down the Edo-period storage houses and sake breweries (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kurayoshi"]]},")"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Enchoen Garden"]},", an authentic Chinese garden built in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["China"]]}," and then reconstructed on site (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Yurihama"]]},")"]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Hakuto Beach"]}," This beach is written about in the Kojiki, Japan's oldest book of history. (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tottori"]]},")"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Yoshioka Hot Spring"]}," Discovered 1,000 years ago. (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tottori"]]},")"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Mount Daisen"]}," Hike on the mountainside, climb up, or ski down the beautiful ",{"type":"'''","value":["Fuji of the West"]}," (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Daisen (Tottori)"],["Daisen"]]},")"]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\nLocal specialties include crab, squid, pears, melons, shallots, and sake.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\t \n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Go next"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hyogo"]]}," Prefecture borders Tottori to the east. Closest to Tottori are ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Toyooka"]]}," City with the famous ",{"type":"'''","value":["Kinosaki Hot Springs"]},", the remains of ",{"type":"'''","value":["Izushi Castle"]},", and the interesting ",{"type":"'''","value":["Japan-Mongolia Folk Museum"]},". In ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Asago"]]}," you can visit the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Takeda Castle Ruins"]},". Although they are ruins, they are well-preserved and the view is great. Further down in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hyogo"]]}," Prefecture you'll find ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Himeji"]]},", famous for the spectacular ",{"type":"'''","value":["Himeji Castle"]},", the port city of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kobe"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kyoto (prefecture)"]]}," lies to the east on the other side of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hyogo"]]},". Although ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kyoto"]]}," City is rather far, ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Amanohashidate"]]}," is quite close and easy to access from Tottori Prefecture. This city is famous as the site of one of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Japan's Top 3"]]},". It is the view from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Amanohashidate"]]}," that is considered to be one of the top 3 views in Japan.\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Okayama Prefecture"]]}," holds Tottori up from the south. ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tsuyama"]]}," with the famous ",{"type":"'''","value":["Kakuzan Park"]},", ",{"type":"'''","value":["Shurakuen Garden"]},", and ",{"type":"'''","value":["Joto Street"]}," is near the eastern region, while ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Niimi"]]},", famous for the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Ikura Ravine"]}," and ",{"type":"'''","value":["Maki Cave"]}," is near Western Tottori. Further south, you'll find the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kurashiki"]]}," with its well-preserved historic district, ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Okayama"]]}," which has one of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Japan's Top 3"]]},", ",{"type":"'''","value":["Korakuen Garden"]},", and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Takahashi"]]},", home to ",{"type":"'''","value":["Bitchu Matsuyama Castle"]},", Japan's highest castle, as well as one of it's only remaining original castles.\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Shimane"]]}," Prefecture stands beside Tottori on the Western border. The most famous sites are close to Tottori, so accessing them is quite convenient. ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Matsue"]]}," is famous for ",{"type":"'''","value":["Matsue Castle"]},", one of Japan's few remaining original castles, and the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Lafcadio Hearn Residence"]},". The city of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Izumo"]]}," is home to the spectacular ",{"type":"'''","value":["Izumo Shrine"]},", the second most holy Shinto shrine in Japan. The ",{"type":"'''","value":["Hinomisaki Lighthouse"]}," is also a famous icon of the city. Further out in the prefecture you'll find ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tsuwano"]]},", where the last Christian martyrs were killed before ending the ban on Christianity and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Oda"]]},"'s Iwami Ginzan, a World Heritage Site. \n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["WikiPedia:Tottori Prefecture"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Dmoz:Regional\/Asia\/Japan\/Prefectures\/Tottori\/"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["geo"],["35.4500"],["133.7667"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["IsPartOf"],["Chugoku"]]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["outlineregion"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Commons:Category:Tottori prefecture"]]}]